@bfredl Yes, I absolutely like your recent UI improvements, and believe that they are showcasing that the neovim work is really starting to pay off.
To emphasize this, the out-of-box experience should be as good as possible. Of course, some consensus and solid implementations for defaults is fundamental.
Good work!
